&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Volatility Trading Developer&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Equity Volatility business is currently seeking a Developer to join in New York. The Developer will work closely with Volatility traders, software developers, quants, and operational teams to develop and optimize tools for managing intraday trading inputs, enhance real-time risk monitoring systems, automate trading processes, and support critical daily trading operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with traders to implement and scale trading strategies, build bespoke datasets, automate execution workflows, and develop tools that integrate trading signals into the execution stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and maintain tools supporting daily trading inputs, including earnings, dividends, interest rates, and quant model parameters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and manage critical trade lifecycle processes, including Early Exercise and Expiration workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modernize legacy systems across risk, P&amp;amp;L, operations, execution, and trading system monitoring to improve reliability, scalability, and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose and resolve issues across trading, quantitative, and risk systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related quantitative field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong programming proficiency in Python, Java, or C++.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SQL or other database languages a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to diagnose complex technical issues, identify root causes, and implement durable, scalable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with a proactive, collaborative, and trader-focused mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, with the ability to operate effectively in high-impact, high-leverage situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$175,000 base salary plus a competitive bonus and comprehensive benefits package.&lt;/p&gt;
